## Second opinion (scope: Tier 1 (cycle modifies .tdd/tdd-config.json + .claude/hooks/require-tdd-state.sh), model: gpt-5.5)

{
  "summary": "Found multiple P0 governance failures: first completions can deadlock, Bash can bypass review gates, and test/production audit checks still accept forged/legacy evidence.",
  "findings": [
    {
      "id": "F1",
      "severity": "P0",
      "category": "correctness",
      "title": "Fresh plan/production review completions are rejected because first audit entry has empty prev_audit_sha",
      "evidence": "run-second-opinion initializes prev_audit_sha to empty when the audit log is absent, stores that empty value in the approved entry, then appends the first obligation_completed audit row with prev_sha empty. The plan hook rejects any approved candidate with empty binding.prev_audit_sha, and the production hook rejects empty prev_audit_sha when an obligation_completed event exists. A normal first review in a fresh cycle therefore cannot unblock the retry.",
      "recommendation": "Allow the chain head case: require a matching obligation_completed audit row with prev_sha == \"\" only when it is the first chained line and verify-audit-chain.sh passes, or seed the audit log before writing the completion so prev_audit_sha is always non-empty.",
      "location": ".claude/hooks/second-opinion-plan-trigger.sh:154"
    },
    {
      "id": "F2",
      "severity": "P0",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Bash writes can bypass no-discretion review before the change lands",
      "evidence": "The Bash pretrigger only treats a narrow regex as mutating: redirection, tee, sed -i, awk -i, cp/mv/rm/touch. Commands such as python/perl/ruby one-liners, dd of=, install, or a shell script can write gated files without matching line 45. The PostToolUse backstop only creates an obligation after the file is already changed, and it ignores test/plan paths entirely.",
      "recommendation": "When no_discretion is enabled, block or require review for broad Bash mutation classes unless an allowlisted read-only command is proven. Extend the posttool backstop to detect plan/test mutations too, but keep it as defense in depth, not the primary gate.",
      "location": ".claude/hooks/second-opinion-bash-pretrigger.sh:45"
    },
    {
      "id": "F3",
      "severity": "P0",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Test review completion accepts any audit line containing the id",
      "evidence": "The test trigger accepts a candidate when grep finds \"exception_id\":\"$candidate_id\" in the audit log, and if binding.prev_audit_sha is empty it performs no chain, event, review_type, scope_hash, or cycle validation. A forged approved test_review_completion can be paired with an unrelated or hand-written audit row for the same id and unblock test writes.",
      "recommendation": "Match the plan hook's strict model: jq-parse audit rows, require event == obligation_completed, exception_id, cycle_id, review_type == test_review, scope_hash all match, and verify the full audit chain.",
      "location": ".claude/hooks/second-opinion-test-trigger.sh:139"
    },
    {
      "id": "F4",
      "severity": "P0",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Production review completion still accepts legacy granted audit events",
      "evidence": "The production hook accepts audit events where event is obligation_completed or granted, then treats empty stored_prev as a v1.7 legacy event and sets chain_ok=true. Review-completion entries are v1.9 artifacts, so a granted event is never valid proof that the runner reviewed the production scope.",
      "recommendation": "Remove the granted fallback for production_edit_review_completion. Require a runner-written obligation_completed event with matching exception_id, cycle_id, review_type, scope_hash, and valid prev_sha chain linkage.",
      "location": ".claude/hooks/second-opinion-production-trigger.sh:170"
